I stand before the court today to plead guilty to the offense of accepting a bribe. I am aware of the severity of my actions and take full responsibility for my involvement in this matter.

I was offered a sum of £4000 in exchange for not publishing an article that exposed the true emissions of a company. As an investigative journalist, I had discovered that this company was emitting one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than what they claimed. While I admit to accepting the bribe, I firmly believe that the consequences of my actions were limited.

The publication of the article would have undoubtedly revealed the company's deception and potentially held them accountable for their actions. However, it is important to note that the true emissions data was later released by another source just five weeks after my involvement. Therefore, the impact of my actions in allowing the greenwashing of the company to continue was brief and mitigated by subsequent disclosures.

I would like to emphasize that, prior to this incident, I had a clean record with no prior involvement in criminal activities. I respectfully request the court to consider my guilty plea and my exemplary record as mitigating factors in this case.

I acknowledge the seriousness of the offense I committed and the potential damage it could have caused. I assure the court that I deeply regret my lapse in judgment, and I am committed to learning from this experience and taking the necessary steps to prevent any future involvement in similar offenses.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I plead guilty to the offense of accepting a bribe and accept the consequences of my actions. I trust that the court will consider the mitigating factors presented and exercise its discretion in determining a just and fair outcome.

Thank you for your attention.

